         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">16 April 1866. ¶  ¶ I am directed by the Honorable the Chief Secretary to inform you that whenever it is necessary for your Department to make a remittance to the Crown Agent: it is desirable that an ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">66.04.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Moore</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">N2304, no. 1302, p. 94, unit 11, VPRS 1187/P outward correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Similar letters were sent to other Heads of Departments. The original letter, addressed to the Chairman of the Board of Agriculture is no. 1302, pp. 93-4.</p>
               </note>16 April 1866.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am directed by the Honorable the Chief Secretary to inform you that whenever it is necessary for your Department to make a remittance to the Crown Agent: it is desirable that an account be prepared on the usual form and in the name of the Honorable the Treasurer, as the claimant, and that it be forwarded to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">this office</hi>
               </seg> in sufficient time to admit of its being sent to the Treasury, at least a week before the Mail closes, in a letter containing the Chief Secretary's approval of the remittance being made.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">(Sd) J. Moore</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Director of the Botanic Gardens.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Circulars similar to this one were sent to fourteen Heads of Departments.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
